!theme plain

entity StatusLookup {
 * statusId : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 statusType : VARCHAR(20)
 code : VARCHAR(30)
}

entity User {
 * user_id : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 name : VARCHAR(100)
 email : VARCHAR(100)
 phone : VARCHAR(20)
}

entity Developer {
 * developerId : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 name : VARCHAR(100)
 role : VARCHAR(50)
 responsibility : VARCHAR(200)
}

entity Flight {
 * flightId : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 origin : VARCHAR(100)
 destination : VARCHAR(100)
 departureTime : TIMESTAMP
 arrivalTime : TIMESTAMP
 statusId : INT <<FK>>
}

entity Booking {
 * bookingId : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 user_id : INT <<FK>>
 flightId : INT <<FK>>
 bookingDate : TIMESTAMP
 statusId : INT <<FK>>
}

entity Ticket {
 * ticketId : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 bookingId : INT <<FK>>
 seatNumber : VARCHAR(20)
 company : VARCHAR(100)
 price : NUMERIC(10,2)
 issueDate : TIMESTAMP
 isPremium : BOOLEAN
}

entity InsurancePolicy {
 * policyId : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 bookingId : INT <<FK>>
 coverageAmount : NUMERIC(10,2)
 premium : NUMERIC(10,2)
 statusId : INT <<FK>>
}

entity Payment {
 * paymentId : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 bookingId : INT <<FK>>
 amount : NUMERIC(10,2)
 paymentMethod : VARCHAR(50)
 paymentDate : TIMESTAMP
 statusId : INT <<FK>>
}

entity InsuranceClaim {
 * claimId : SERIAL <<PK>>
 --
 policyId : INT <<FK>>
 delayDuration : FLOAT
 claimStatus : VARCHAR(50)
 payoutAmount : NUMERIC(10,2)
}

' ======================================================
' RELATIONSHIPS (Based exactly on your SQL schema)
' ======================================================

User ||--o{ Booking : \"makes\"

Flight ||--o{ Booking : \"booked in\"

StatusLookup ||--o{ Flight : \"status\"

StatusLookup ||--o{ Booking : \"status\"

Booking ||--o{ Ticket : \"issues\"

Booking ||--o{ InsurancePolicy : \"has\"

Booking ||--o{ Payment : \"paid with\"

StatusLookup ||--o{ InsurancePolicy : \"status\"

StatusLookup ||--o{ Payment : \"status\"

InsurancePolicy ||--o{ InsuranceClaim : \"generates\"

@enduml
